servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Thinly slice half the @jalapeño{1} into rounds; mince remaining jalapeño. Dice @roma tomato{1}(diced).

> TIP: Remove ribs and seeds for less heat.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a large #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and minced jalapeño to taste. Season with @salt{}. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add @ground turkey{10%oz} and @Southwest spice blend{2%tbsp} to pot with aromatics; season with salt and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until turkey is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir diced tomato, @tomato paste{1.5%oz}, and @Tex-Mex paste{1} into pot until slightly darkened in color, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @black beans{13.4%oz} and their liquid, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @water{1/4%cup}, salt, and pepper; stir to combine. Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn off heat.

> TIP: If chili is too thick, add another splash of water. For 4 servings, use ½ cup water instead of ¼ cup.

Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide chili between bowls. Top with @smoky red pepper crema{2%tbsp}, scallion greens, and as much sliced jalapeño as you like. Serve.

> If you've got some on hand, consider crumbling up some tortilla chips and sprinkling them on top for a crunch!